                    gobject.CClosure.new(@ptrCast(p_callback), p_data, @ptrCast(p_options.destroyData)),
                    @intFromBool(p_options.after),
                );
            }
        };
    };

    /// Query the section that covers the given position. The number of
    /// items in the section can be computed by `out_end - out_start`.
    ///
    /// If the position is larger than the number of items, a single
    /// range from n_items to G_MAXUINT will be returned.
    extern fn gtk_section_model_get_section(p_self: *SectionModel, p_position: c_uint, p_out_start: *c_uint, p_out_end: *c_uint) void;
    pub const getSection = gtk_section_model_get_section;

    /// This function emits the `gtk.SectionModel.signals.sections_changed`
    /// signal to notify about changes to sections.
